Overview
========

The Lambda Programming Language is a baby programming language (as in,
it's a wee little language, not a language for babies.) It runs in an
interactive execution environment. It implements lambda calculus.

Requirements
============

The Lambda Programming Language requires the Vrui VR development
toolkit, version 15.0-001 or later, and therefore runs on UNIX-like
operating systems.
Technically speaking, the Lambda Programming Language only requires
the Misc and Threads sub-libraries of the Vrui VR development toolkit,
but who's keeping track.

Quick Installation Guide for the Impatient
==========================================

0. Install the Vrui VR toolkit. Note the path to Vrui's build system,
   printed at the beginning of Vrui's build process. By default, the
   path is /usr/local/share/Vrui-<version>/make.

1. Clone or download the Lambda Programming Language's git repository,
   say into ~/src/Lambda.

2. Change into the  Lambda Programming Language's base directory, say
   > cd ~/src/Lambda

3. Build the Lambda Programming Language
   > make VRUI_MAKEDIR=<path to Vrui's build system>

4. Run the Lambda Programming Language
   > ./bin/Lambda
